    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.18.11"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">SIGURD NEIHARDT COLLECTION</hi></note>
                <fw type="curatorial"><del/><add>11</add></fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Coat of Arms of Mount Saint Joseph</figDesc>
                        <p>SOLI DEO GLORIA <unclear cert="high"><unclear/> AD JUSTITIAM <unclear/> MULTOS FULG<unclear/></unclear></p>
                    </figure>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">MOUNT SAINT JOSEPH
                        <lb/>
                    MAPLE MOUNT, KENTUCKY</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Oct. 25th, 1939.</dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It is with great sorrow in my heart heart as a lover of the beautiful in literature and from your pen that I must inform you that we could not possibly meet $50.00. That is a lot of money for a little struggling school like ours. I would not ask you to even think of coming for what we could pay, which would only be $20.00 or at most $25.00. It was foolheardy<sic>foolhardy</sic> on my part ever to have such aspirations but we often let our heart run away with our heads, especially when we love the beautiful.</p>
                
                <p>The sacrifice that will be mine in not hearing you will be offered for the success of your work; that "The Giver of All Good Gifts" may bless you abundantly and from your pen, things of greater beauty may be created.</p>
                
                <p>The time would have been lovely, either in the afternoon or evening. If you ever pass through Owensboro, which is only fifteen miles from us, we hope that you will come visit us and even spend the night with us.</p>
                
                <p>God bless you for the beautiful things you have given to the world and may you live long to continue in the great work.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very cordially</salute>
                    <signed>Sister M. Josephine</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
